                             MIKE-IN-HAND RADIO!
                              **NEW FREQUENCY**
             THE NATIONAL WEATHER SERVICE OFFICE YAKUTAT ALASKA
                  ANNOUNCES A NEW RADIO SERVICE FOR PILOTS.
                           CONTACT US DIRECTLY ON
                                    122.0
   FOR YOUR OFFICIAL FLIGHT WEATHER BRIEFINGS, CURRENT WEATHER CONDITIONS
                            OR TO SUBMIT PIREPS!
                       ALSO CALL US AT: 1-907-784-3322
                                     OR
                CALL 1-800-WXBRIEF TO  FILE YOUR FLIGHT PLAN
                         AND OBTAIN CURRENT WEATHER
                       NOAA WEATHER RADIO AND YAKUTAT
              YOU CAN TUNE INTO YOUR LOCAL WEATHER  ANYTIME BY
                LISTENING TO NOAA WEATHER RADIO.  IN YAKUTAT
                WE  BROADCAST AT A FREQUENCY OF  162.40 MHz.
                On the Marine VHF Radio tune into Channel 2!
                     No Radio?  No Problem!   Call  the
                             Alaska Weather Line


                      In Alaska call:    1-800-472-0391
                                  In Juneau call:             790-6850
                                    In Anchorage call:       266-5145
                                   In Fairbanks call:         458-3745
                                    OUT OF STATE       1-907-266-5165

